<section xml:id="section-more-det-terminology">

<title>Terminology and notation</title>

<introduction><p> The following definitions apply to a square matrix <m>A</m>. </p></introduction>

<p><dl width="narrow">

	<li>
	<title>matrix of cofactors</title>
	<idx><h>matrix</h><h>of cofactors</h></idx>
	<idx><h>cofactor</h><h>matrix</h></idx>
	<p> the matrix obtained by replacing all the entries of <m>A</m> with the corresponding cofactors of <m>A</m>, denoted <m>C_A</m> </p>
	</li>

	<li>
	<title>(classical) adjoint matrix</title>
	<idx><h>adjoint</h><h>classical</h></idx>
	<idx><h>matrix</h><h>adjoint (classical)</h></idx>
	<p>the transpose of the matrix of cofactors of <m>A</m>, denoted <m>\adj A</m></p>
	</li>

</dl></p>

</section>
